---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Base
  title="Resume — Alexandros Karatzaferis"
  description="Software Architect with 10+ years making teams ship more and fight less. Principal-level experience across SaaS, remote orgs, and different company stages."
  canonical="https://duditeria.com/resume"
>
  <header class="top-bar fade-in">
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Duditeria</a>
    <span class="header-title">Resume</span>
  </header>

  <main>
    <div class="bento">

      <!-- ── 1. NAME ───────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <div class="card card-name" data-reveal style="--d:0">
        <p class="name-eyebrow">Making teams ship more and fight less</p>
        <h1 class="name-text">Alexandros<br>Karatzaferis</h1>
        <p class="name-sub">Software Architect · 10+ years · Athens</p>
      </div>

      <!-- ── 2. PHOTO ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <!--
        Drop your photo at public/photo.jpg — the card will fill automatically.
        Until then it shows the AK monogram.
      -->
      <div class="card card-photo" data-reveal style="--d:1">
        <img src="/alex.webp" alt="Alexandros Karatzaferis" class="photo-img" />
      </div>

      <!-- ── 3. EXPERIENCE (spans rows 1+2) ────────────────────────── -->
      <div class="card card-exp" data-reveal style="--d:2">
        <h2 class="card-label">Experience</h2>

        <div class="tl">

          <div class="tl-item">
            <div class="tl-head">
              <div>
                <span class="tl-role">Software Architect</span>
                <span class="tl-company">THEFUTUREOFJEWELRY · Remote</span>
              </div>
              <span class="tl-dates">Feb 2020 – Present</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="tl-bullets">
              <li>Designed and owned the core product architecture for five years — stable enough to absorb major product pivots without rewrites, and trusted enough that engineering decisions rarely needed defending.</li>
              <li>Reframed technical debt from a morale problem into a shared roadmap — the team stopped treating it as someone else's problem and started treating it as part of the work.</li>
              <li>Mentored a 7-person engineering team and represented the discipline at the C-suite — translating product uncertainty into technical direction, and technical trade-offs into business language.</li>
              <li>Kept the architecture simple enough that new engineers were shipping within their first week — KISS wasn't a wall poster, it was how we actually built.</li>
              <li>Brought AI coding agents into the workflow early — before it was fashionable — raising junior engineer productivity by ~25% and freeing the whole team to focus on harder problems.</li>
              <li>Established two-week sprints to build delivery habits, then let the team outgrow them — deploys moved to business rhythm rather than calendar pressure, which suited both the product and the team.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="tl-item">
            <div class="tl-head">
              <div>
                <span class="tl-role">Software Engineer</span>
                <span class="tl-company">Viral Loops · Athens</span>
              </div>
              <span class="tl-dates">Jan 2018 – Jan 2020</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="tl-bullets">
              <li>Owned feature development end-to-end on a viral marketing platform — picked up an unfamiliar codebase fast and shipped reliably without handholding.</li>
              <li>Worked at real production scale: thousands of concurrent users, sharp spikes during campaign launches, and background jobs that couldn't slip under pressure.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="tl-item">
            <div class="tl-head">
              <div>
                <span class="tl-role">Node.js Software Engineer</span>
                <span class="tl-company">wappier · Athens</span>
              </div>
              <span class="tl-dates">Jan – Dec 2017</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="tl-bullets">
              <li>Full-stack engineer on a MongoDB–Node–Angular revenue management platform — learned the stack, found my footing quickly, and contributed without drama.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="tl-item">
            <div class="tl-head">
              <div>
                <span class="tl-role">Front-End Developer</span>
                <span class="tl-company">University of São Paulo – IPEN · Athens</span>
              </div>
              <span class="tl-dates">Sep 2015 – Dec 2016</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="tl-bullets">
              <li>Built a scientific crystal-structure visualization tool for researchers — a domain I knew nothing about before I started, which turned out to be the point.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ── 4. ABOUT ME ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <div class="card card-about" data-reveal style="--d:3">
        <h2 class="card-label">About</h2>
        <p class="about-text">
          Most engineers move toward either the code or the people. I've always done both, because I've seen what breaks when you separate them. Over 10 years across different team sizes and company stages, I've learned that the best systems aren't just well-architected — they're built by teams who trust each other and know what they're building toward.
        </p>
        <p class="about-text">
          I've spent the last five years as the architect who still reads the code, mentors the engineers, and sits in the room when the business makes decisions that affect the team. The thread isn't a stack or a domain — it's getting teams to a place where shipping feels natural and the work actually matters.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- ── 5. CONTACT LINK ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <a href="/contact" class="card card-contact" data-reveal style="--d:4">
        <span class="contact-label">Wanna get in touch?</span>
        <div class="contact-cta">
          <span class="contact-cta-text">Contact Me</span>
          <span class="contact-arrow">↗</span>
        </div>
      </a>

      <!-- ── 6. FEATURED WORK ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <a href="https://github.com/ekaratzaferis" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="card card-work" data-reveal style="--d:7">
        <h2 class="work-label">Featured Work</h2>
        <div class="work-visual">
          <div class="work-screen">
            <div class="work-screen-bar">
              <span></span><span></span><span></span>
            </div>
            <div class="work-screen-body">
              <div class="work-line w-80"></div>
              <div class="work-line w-60"></div>
              <div class="work-line w-90"></div>
              <div class="work-line w-40"></div>
              <div class="work-line w-70"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="work-footer">
          <span>github.com/ekaratzaferis</span>
          <span class="work-arrow">↗</span>
        </div>
      </a>

      <!-- ── 7. GOING DEEP ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <div class="card card-explore" data-reveal style="--d:6">
        <h2 class="card-label">Going Deep</h2>
        <p class="explore-why">
          Before I use something, I try to understand what it actually is. I went deep on things like the JS event loop and Python's GIL. Now I'm doing the same with AI — learning the math and mechanics from the ground up, because I want to work <em>on</em> this technology, not just with it.
        </p>
        <div class="explore-topics">
          <span class="explore-tag">Linear Algebra</span>
          <span class="explore-tag">Neural Networks</span>
          <span class="explore-tag">Backpropagation</span>
          <span class="explore-tag">Transformers</span>
          <span class="explore-tag">Attention</span>
          <span class="explore-tag">CNNs</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ── 8. SKILLS / TOOLBOX ─────────────────────────────────── -->
      <div class="card card-skills" data-reveal style="--d:8">
        <h2 class="card-label">Toolbox</h2>
        <div class="toolbox">
          <div class="tool-box">Node.js</div>
          <div class="tool-box">JS</div>
          <div class="tool-box">React</div>
          <div class="tool-box">MongoDB</div>
          <div class="tool-box">REST</div>
          <div class="tool-box">Cloud</div>
          <div class="tool-box">Docker</div>
          <div class="tool-box">Git</div>
          <div class="tool-box">AI&nbsp;/&nbsp;LLM</div>
          <div class="tool-box">SaaS</div>
          <div class="tool-box">Arch.</div>
          <div class="tool-box">Agile</div>
          <div class="tool-box">Python</div>
          <div class="tool-box">Redis</div>
          <div class="tool-box">Kubernetes</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ── 8. EDUCATION + EXTRAS ──────────────────────────────── -->
      <div class="card card-edu" data-reveal style="--d:5">

        <section class="edu-block">
          <h2 class="card-label">Education</h2>
          <p class="edu-degree">Electronic &amp; Computer Engineering</p>
          <p class="edu-school">Technical University of Crete</p>
          <p class="edu-detail">B.Eng. · 2007 – 2015</p>
        </section>

        <section class="edu-block">
          <h2 class="card-label" style="margin-top:1.5rem">Languages</h2>
          <div class="lang-row">
            <span class="lang-name">English</span>
            <span class="lang-level">Bilingual</span>
          </div>
          <div class="lang-row">
            <span class="lang-name">Greek</span>
            <span class="lang-level">Native</span>
          </div>
        </section>

      </div>

    </div>
  </main>
</Base>

<script>
  const cards = document.querySelectorAll('[data-reveal]');
  const io = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => {
      entries.forEach((entry) => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          entry.target.classList.add('visible');
          io.unobserve(entry.target);
        }
      });
    },
    { threshold: 0.06, rootMargin: '0px 0px -20px 0px' }
  );
  cards.forEach((c) => io.observe(c));
</script>

<style>
  /* ── Scroll ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  :global(html), :global(body) { overflow: auto; height: auto; }

  /* ── Top bar ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .top-bar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    height: 3rem;
    padding: 0 2rem;
    background: #000;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 10;
  }

  .back-link {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #888;
    white-space: nowrap;
    transition: color 0.25s ease;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: #ccc;
  }

  .header-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  /* ── Page ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  main {
    padding: 1.5rem 1.25rem 4rem;
    max-width: 1160px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* ── Grid ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .bento {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1.6fr;
    grid-template-areas:
      "name      photo    exp"
      "about     contact  exp"
      "about     edu      exp"
      "exploring featured exp"
      "toolbox   featured exp";
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .card-name    { grid-area: name; }
  .card-photo   { grid-area: photo; }
  .card-exp     { grid-area: exp; }
  .card-about   { grid-area: about; }
  .card-contact { grid-area: contact; }
  .card-work    { grid-area: featured; }
  .card-skills  { grid-area: toolbox; }
  .card-edu     { grid-area: edu; }
  .card-explore { grid-area: exploring; }

  /* ── Card base ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .card {
    background: #0c0c0c;
    border: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
    display: block;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;

    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(18px);
    transition:
      opacity      0.55s ease calc(var(--d, 0) * 60ms),
      transform    0.55s ease calc(var(--d, 0) * 60ms),
      border-color 0.22s ease,
      box-shadow   0.22s ease;
  }

  .card.visible { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }

  .card.visible:hover {
    border-color: #2a2a2a;
    box-shadow: 0 16px 48px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.55);
    transform: translateY(-4px);
  }

  /* ── Section label ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .card-label {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.28em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #888;
    margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.55rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
  }

  /* ── 1. Name card ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .card-name {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    min-height: 160px;
    background: #080808;
    padding: 2rem 2.25rem;
  }

  .name-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #888;
    margin-bottom: auto;
  }

  .name-text {
    font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 5vw, 3.4rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #f0f0f0;
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .name-sub {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #666;
  }

  /* ── 2. Photo card ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .card-photo {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    padding: 0;
    min-height: 390px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: #0a0a0a;
  }

  .photo-img {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: 40% 10%;
    border-radius: 11px;
  }

  .photo-fallback {
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: #333;
    user-select: none;
    /* hidden when photo loads */
  }

  /* ── 3. Experience card ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .card-exp {
    padding: 2rem 2.25rem;
  }

  .tl {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2.2rem;
  }

  .tl-head {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
  }

  .tl-role {
    display: block;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: #e0e0e0;
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }

  .tl-company {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #888;
  }

  .tl-dates {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: #666;
    white-space: nowrap;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    padding-top: 0.15rem;
  }

  .tl-bullets {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .tl-bullets li {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #c0c0c0;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .tl-bullets li::before {
    content: '–';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #555;
  }

  /* ── 4. About card ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .card-about {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.9rem;
  }

  .about-text {
    font-size: 0.97rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #c0c0c0;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  /* ── 5. Contact link card ────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .card-contact {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: space-between;
    cursor: pointer;
    min-height: 160px;
  }

  .contact-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #888;
  }

  .contact-cta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .contact-cta-text {
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.8rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #e0e0e0;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .card-contact:hover .contact-cta-text { color: #ffffff; }

  .contact-arrow {
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    color: #555;
    transition: color 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }

  .card-contact:hover .contact-arrow {
    color: #ccc;
    transform: translate(3px, -3px);
  }

  /* ── 6. Featured work card ───────────────────────────────────────── */
  .card-work {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    min-height: 200px;
  }

  .work-label {
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 2.5vw, 2.2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #e8e8e8;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .card-work:hover .work-label { color: #ffffff; }

  /* Fake laptop mockup */
  .work-visual {
    flex: 1;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .work-screen {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 200px;
    background: #111;
    border: 1px solid #222;
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .work-screen-bar {
    display: flex;
    gap: 4px;
    padding: 6px 8px;
    background: #181818;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #222;
  }

  .work-screen-bar span {
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #2a2a2a;
  }

  .work-screen-body {
    padding: 10px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 5px;
  }

  .work-line {
    height: 5px;
    background: #222;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .w-80 { width: 80%; }
  .w-60 { width: 60%; }
  .w-90 { width: 90%; }
  .w-40 { width: 40%; }
  .w-70 { width: 70%; }

  .work-footer {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: #888;
  }

  .work-arrow {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    transition: transform 0.2s, color 0.2s;
  }

  .card-work:hover .work-arrow {
    transform: translate(3px, -3px);
    color: #ccc;
  }

  /* ── 7. Skills / Toolbox card ────────────────────────────────────── */
  .toolbox {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 5px;
  }

  .tool-box {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    border: 1px solid #222;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #aaa;
    background: #0a0a0a;
    text-align: center;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, color 0.2s, background 0.2s;
  }

  .tool-box:hover {
    border-color: #3a3a3a;
    color: #f0f0f0;
    background: #111;
  }

  /* ── 8. Education card ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .card-edu {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .edu-block { flex-shrink: 0; }

  .edu-degree {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #e0e0e0;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .edu-school {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #888;
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }

  .edu-detail {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: #555;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .lang-row {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: baseline;
    padding: 0.42rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #141414;
  }
  .lang-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .lang-name {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #d0d0d0;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  .lang-level {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #666;
  }

  /* ── Explore card ────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .explore-why {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #c0c0c0;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .explore-topics {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .explore-tag {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.7rem;
    border: 1px solid #222;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #aaa;
    background: #0a0a0a;
  }

  /* ── Responsive — tablet ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .bento {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      grid-template-areas:
        "name      photo"
        "about     contact"
        "about     edu"
        "exp       exp"
        "exploring toolbox"
        "featured  featured";
    }
  }

  /* ── Responsive — mobile ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .bento {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      grid-template-areas:
        "name"
        "photo"
        "about"
        "contact"
        "exp"
        "exploring"
        "toolbox"
        "featured"
        "edu";
    }

    main { padding: 5rem 1rem 3rem; }
    .card { padding: 1.5rem 1.5rem; }
    .card-name { min-height: 200px; }
    .card-photo { min-height: 280px; }
    .card-contact { min-height: 140px; }
  }
</style>
